<div class="max-w-3xl">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About Bethlehem Township Crime Map</h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-crime-muted">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Mission</h2>
      <p>
        The Bethlehem Township Crime Map provides transparent, accessible crime data to help residents
        stay informed about public safety in their community. Our goal is to promote awareness,
        encourage community engagement, and support data-driven public safety initiatives.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Data Sources</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Crime data is collected from publicly available sources including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
        <li>Bethlehem Township Police Department public records</li>
        <li>Pennsylvania State Police crime reporting system</li>
        <li>Public safety bulletins and press releases</li>
        <li>Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) requests</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Privacy & Anonymization</h2>
      <p>
        To protect privacy, specific addresses are generalized to the street block level.
        No personally identifiable information about victims or suspects is displayed.
        All data presented complies with applicable privacy laws and regulations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Technical Implementation</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">This project is built using the KONOMI Standard framework:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
        <li><strong>Static Site Generation:</strong> 11ty (Eleventy)</li>
        <li><strong>Styling:</strong> Tailwind CSS</li>
        <li><strong>Mapping:</strong> Leaflet.js with OpenStreetMap</li>
        <li><strong>Interactivity:</strong> Alpine.js</li>
        <li><strong>Data Format:</strong> KONOMI UDT (User Defined Types)</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> GitHub Pages</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Data Model (UDTs)</h2>
      <div class="bg-crime-surface rounded-lg p-4 border border-crime-primary/30 font-mono text-sm">
        <pre class="text-crime-text">
<span class="text-crime-accent">CrimeIncident</span> {
  id: string
  type: <span class="text-crime-warning">CrimeType</span>
  date: datetime
  location: <span class="text-crime-warning">GeoLocation</span>
  address: string
  description: string
  status: <span class="text-crime-warning">IncidentStatus</span>
  severity: int (1-5)
}

<span class="text-crime-accent">GeoLocation</span> {
  lat: float
  lng: float
}

<span class="text-crime-accent">Hotspot</span> {
  center: <span class="text-crime-warning">GeoLocation</span>
  radius: float
  incidentCount: int
  intensity: string
  timeframe: string
}
        </pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Updates</h2>
      <p>
        Crime data is updated regularly as new information becomes available from public sources.
        The last update date is displayed in the sidebar. Data typically reflects incidents reported
        within the past 90 days, with historical data available for trend analysis.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-crime-text mb-3">Disclaimer</h2>
      <p class="text-sm">
        This crime map is provided for informational purposes only. While we strive for accuracy,
        data may be incomplete or contain errors. Crime data should not be used as the sole basis
        for making decisions about personal safety or property transactions. For official crime
        statistics and reports, please contact the Bethlehem Township Police Department directly.
      </p>
    </section>

